      • override

        protected T override(IRNode parent,
                     IRNode n)
        Allows to hijack the traversal of a subtree. This function is called by visit(IRNode, IRNode) upon entering node n. If a non-null result r is returned, the traversal is stopped and the result is r. By default, overriding is inactive.

      • enter

        protected AggregateVisitor<T> enter(IRNode parent,
                                    IRNode n)
        Called upon entering n during the AST traversal. This allows to perform certain actions, including returning a new visitor to be used in the subtree.

      • leave

        protected T leave(IRNode parent,
                  IRNode n,
                  T r,
                  AggregateVisitor<T> v_)
        Called after finishing traversal of the subtree rooted at n. When enter(IRNode, IRNode) creates a new visitor to be used on the subtree, the old visitor still receives the call to leave() -- that is, leave() always executed the same number of times as enter(IRNode, IRNode). This node provides the final opportunity of placing an updated node in the output AST.
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent AST node of n or null when it is the root.
        n - The original node in the input AST
        r - The result returned by IRNode.aggregateChildren(AggregateVisitor)
        v_ - The new node visitor created by enter(IRNode, IRNode), or this.
